Nike's online sales surge in days after Kaepernick ad debut|https://www.cnbc.com|https://www.cnbc.com/2018/09/07/nikes-online-sales-surge-in-days-after-kaepernick-ad-debut.html||2018-09-07|Sarah Whitten,Justin Sullivan,Getty Images||While shares of Nike plunged after it released its new ad campaign for the 30th anniversary of "Just Do It," featuring former San Francisco 49ers quarterback Colin Kaepernick, its sales of apparel and shoes have not.

Despite backlash and boycotts by some consumers, Nike's online sales actually rose in the days after the advertisement debuted.

Between Sunday and Wednesday, product orders rose 27 percent, according Edison Trends, a digital-commerce researcher. In the same period last year, product orders fell 2 percent.
